Crust: Combine Shreddies with butter. Transfer to 9-inch (23 cm) pie plate; press firmly into bottom and up sides. Bake at 350 degrees F (180 degrees C) for 10 min. Cool. Filling: Sprinkle bacon and cheese over crust. Whisk eggs with cream, black pepper, and nutmeg; gently pour into crust. Bake 35 min. or until knife inserted in centre comes out clean. Cool 5 min. before cutting.